BACKGROUND: Obesity and knee osteoarthritis are among the most frequent chronic 
conditions affecting Americans aged 50 to 84 years.
OBJECTIVE: To estimate quality-adjusted life-years lost due to obesity and knee 
osteoarthritis and health benefits of reducing obesity prevalence to levels 
observed a decade ago.
