persons aged 50 to 84 years to 4 subpopulations: nonobese without knee 
osteoarthritis (reference group), nonobese with knee osteoarthritis, obese 
without knee osteoarthritis, and obese with knee osteoarthritis. The 
Osteoarthritis Policy Model, a computer simulation model of knee osteoarthritis 
and obesity, was used to estimate quality-adjusted life-year losses due to knee 
